{
  "info": {
    "name": "AirportSystem \u2013 Flight Service",
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "description": "Full test coverage for the Flight Service GraphQL API via the YARP gateway.\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Start the stack: `docker compose up`\n2. Run **Login \u2013 Staff** (or Admin/Passenger) to populate auth tokens automatically.\n3. All subsequent requests use `{{staffToken}}` / `{{adminToken}}` / `{{passengerToken}}`.\n\n**Subscriptions** are WebSocket requests. Open them in Postman's WebSocket view.\nAuthenticated subscriptions pass the token via `?access_token={{staffToken}}` in the URL.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "gatewayUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:5000/graphql",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "keycloakUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080/realms/airport-system/protocol/openid-connect/token",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "staffToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
